{
  "slug": "onboarding-is-a-production-system",
  "title": "Onboarding is a production system",
  "category": "leadership",
  "kicker": "Team scaling",
  "hook": "A new hire should not have to reverse-engineer your company by reading old Slack threads.",
  "readMinutes": 5,
  "date": "2026-06-19",
  "tags": [
    "onboarding",
    "documentation"
  ],
  "beats": [
    {
      "num": "01 · the shape",
      "heading": "The first week teaches the real culture",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">If setup is broken, docs are stale, and nobody knows who owns the plan, the new engineer learns that the team survives by guessing.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "terminal",
          "title": "onboarding · day one",
          "caption": "The useful signal is usually already there.",
          "lines": [
            {
              "t": "$ ./setup.sh",
              "c": "pr"
            },
            {
              "t": "OK node, db, env, seed data",
              "c": ""
            },
            {
              "t": "next: first good issue linked",
              "c": ""
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "02 · the move",
      "heading": "Make the path executable",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">A good onboarding plan has a working setup script, a first task, named buddies, system maps, and checkpoints for questions that do not fit the docs.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "file": "onboarding/checklist.md",
          "code": "- Run setup and verify local app\n- Ship one docs-only PR\n- Pair on one customer-facing bug\n- Map the services touched by checkout",
          "caption": "The checklist should create motion, not homework."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "03 · the check",
      "heading": "Update it from real friction",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Every new hire is a fresh test run. When they get stuck, fix the system, not just their laptop.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "stats",
          "items": [
            {
              "to": 1,
              "label": "first task ready before start date"
            },
            {
              "to": 2,
              "label": "buddies: domain and culture"
            },
            {
              "to": 30,
              "label": "days to revisit the plan"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "04 · the takeaway",
      "heading": "Onboarding compounds",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">A strong onboarding system turns each new hire into both a contributor and a debugger of the team itself.</p>"
        },
